 UFT Protocol

 The UFT protocol (Universal File Transfer or Unsolicited File Transfer)
 is suitable for sending files between unlike systems over any stream
 oriented sub-protocol,  like TCP.


UFT      FILE           The FILE command starts a file
UFT      USER           The USER command identifies recipient
UFT      TYPE           The TYPE command type (A or I)
UFT      NAME           The NAME command names the file
UFT      DATA           The DATA command
UFT      EOF            The EOF command signals end-of-file
UFT      QUIT           The QUIT command terminates the session
UFT      UFTTYPES       TYPE values (canonicalization values)
UFT      CPQ            The CPQ command (VM servers only)
UFT      MSG            The MSG command (VM servers only)
